= Using Tor Browser without Tor =

[[Tor Browser]] is based on Firefox and implements a large number of changes for enhanced security and privacy. It routes all traffic through [https://www.torproject.org/about/overview.html Tor], which can prevent the recipients of your communications from seeing that you sent it. Disabling Tor means that your IP address is not hidden anymore. But Tor Browser without Tor will still protect you better than Firefox, Chrome/Chromium and Microsoft Edge from numerous other [[Data Collection Techniques|data collection techniques]] as described in ''[https://www.torproject.org/projects/torbrowser/design/ The Design and Implementation of the Tor Browser].''

