=== Making Tor Browser more...normal ===

<ul>
<li><p>'''How to set preferences?''' Click on the three horizontal bars in the upper-right corner of the Tor Browser window. Select 'Preferences' in the menu that pops up.</p></li>
<li><p>'''How to prevent Tor Browser from deleting the browsing and download history as well as all cookies when it closes?''' By default Tor Browser always uses private browsing mode. To disable it go to Preferences, click the 'Privacy' tab on the left-hand side and uncheck the box to the left of 'Always use private browsing mode'. The browser needs to restart for the changes to take effect.</p>
<p>NB: When you disable private browsing mode Tor Browser by default keeps cookies 'until they expire'. To increase your privacy you should install some extensions that block tracking cookies: [https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/disconnect/ Disconnect], [https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/privacy-badger17/ Privacy Badger] (browser might need to be restarted for it to work), and, if you want an ad-blocker too, [https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/privacy-badger17/ uBlock Origin]. You may also want to set cookies to be kept 'I close Tor Browser' (also in the Privacy section of Preferences).</p></li>
<li><p>'''How can to make Tor Browser remember passwords?''' Necessary first step: Disable private browsing mode (see above). Then go to Preferences, click the 'Security' tab on the left-hand side and tick the box to the left of 'Remember login for sites'.</p></li></ul>

